{{unreferenced|date=March 2016}}
The '''Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (CSEE)''' is an academic [[O Level ]] [[Test (assessment)|examination]] that is done by Form four students ([[12th grade]]) across [[Tanzania]] to prepare them for their [[A-level|A level]] studies. The exams are usually done between late September to early or mid November and they are managed by the [[National Examinations Council of Tanzania]] (NECTA). Students are required to obtain three credits in order to pass the exams.

